  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I feel like here we'll need to introduce the concept of \"shared widgets\". I don't think we can assume that whenever the attribute names are identical (`color` in this case), we can sum the facet counts.\r\n\r\nAnother solution would be to pass the `scopedResults` to the `transformItems` function. We already had some use cases for accessing search parameters or the UI state in this function. That would make it possible to achieve this behavior user-land.",
